sentences: Tim Moore is an American pop singer and songwriter who recorded four albums for Asylum Records in the 1970s.
During its year of existence, the band did one week residencies at the Trauma, a psychedelic club in Philadelphia, with acts like the Velvet Underground.

Moore's self titled debut solo album came in 1974 as the first release by a label called A Small Record Company.
Moore's version made a brief re-appearance of the Canadian charts in early 1978, reaching number 92.
During 1975 Moore released the album Behind the Eyes.
The song was a hit when re-recorded by the Bay City Rollers a year later.
They became friends and Moore spent two weeks in rehearsals with the Rolling Stones and Peter Tosh at Bearsville Studios in Woodstock.
In 1986 Moore released his fifth album, Flash Forward.
He spent 75 days touring Brazil after "Yes," a ballad from that album, rocketed to No.1 and stayed there for ten weeks.

As of 2019, Moore continues to write songs and plans new recording projects and live dates through 2020.

Two major non-fiction books have been in production for over a decade.
His fine art work will be published as an edition of prints in late 2019.
In 2016, was the music director for an all-star tribute to Lou Reed for the 50th anniversary of Max's Kansas City.
